<subSubSection id="FDAA651F060A2E46FF18F953FF3D23F8" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B50F3694060A2E46FF18F953FF3D23F8" blockId="32.[151,1437,1148,1714]" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86060A2E46FF18F953FEEE21DC" bold="true" box="[151,260,1148,1174]" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="D1214B65060A2E46FE9BF952FE5221DC" author="McLay C. L." box="[276,440,1148,1175]" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" pagination="111 - 251" refId="ref27774" refString="McLay C. L. (1993) Crustacea Decapoda: the sponge crabs (Dromiidae) of New Caledonia and the Philippines with a review of the genera. In: Crosnier, A. (Ed.), Resultats des campagnes MUSORSTOM, volume 10. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, 156, 111 - 251" type="journal article" year="1993">McLay (1993)</bibRefCitation>
revised the genus 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17060A2E46FD1FF953FC0421DC" authority="Borradaile, 1900" authorityName="Borradaile" authorityYear="1900" box="[656,1006,1148,1174]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Dromidiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86060A2E46FD1FF953FCCD21DC" box="[656,807,1148,1174]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Dromidiopsis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D1214B65060A2E46FCBFF953FC0421DC" author="Borradaile, LA" box="[816,1006,1148,1174]" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" pagination="568 - 596" refId="ref24917" refString="Borradaile, LA. (1900) On some crustaceans from the South Pacific. Part IV. The crabs. Proceedings of the Zoological Society London, A, 1900, 568 - 596." type="journal article" year="1900">Borradaile, 1900</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
to include 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17060A2E46FBFEF952FF3821F0" authority="Lamarck, 1818" authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1818" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Dromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosa">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86060A2E46FBFEF952FAC321DC" box="[1137,1321,1148,1174]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Dromia globosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D1214B65060A2E46FABDF953FF3821F0" author="Lamarck, J B" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" refId="ref26942" refString="Lamarck, J B. P. A. de (1818) Histoire naturelle des animaux sans vertebres, presentant les caracteres generaux et particuliers de ces animaux, leur distribution, leurs classes, leurs familles, leurs genres, et la citation des principales especes qui s'y rapportent; precedee d'une introduction offrant la determination des caracteres essentiels de l'Animal, sa distinction du vegetal et des autres corps naturels, enfin, l'Exposition des principes fondamentaux de la zoologie. Vol. 5. Deterville et Verdiere, Paris, 612 pp." type="book" year="1818">Lamarck, 1818</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and five other species. The 
<typeStatus id="6A0B8836060A2E46FD97F98FFD9521F0" box="[536,639,1184,1210]" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17060A2E46FD28F98EFCB421F0" authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1818" box="[679,862,1184,1210]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Dromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosa">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86060A2E46FD28F98EFCB421F0" box="[679,862,1184,1210]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Dromia globosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MNHN 
<accessionNumber id="AAE3AB77060A2E46FC42F98FFBCD21F0" box="[973,1063,1184,1210]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/B22033" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">B22033</accessionNumber>
) consists of the dried remains of a male, CL = 
<quantity id="72489B71060A2E46FEB9F9EBFE772195" box="[310,413,1220,1247]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.11" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" unit="mm" value="21.1">21.1 mm</quantity>
, of unknown provenance. The recognizable fragments fit most closely with specimens labelled 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17060A2E46FF6CF9C7FD9B2049" authority="Stimpson, 1858" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[227,625,1256,1283]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Dromidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excavata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86060A2E46FF6CF9C7FE502048" box="[227,442,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Dromidia excavata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D1214B65060A2E46FE4EF9C7FD9B2049" author="Stimpson, W." box="[449,625,1256,1283]" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" pagination="225 - 252" refId="ref30031" refString="Stimpson, W. (1858) Prodromus descriptionis animalium evertebratorum, quae in expeditione and Oceanum Pacificum Septentrionalem, a Republica Federata missa, Cadwaladaro Ringgold et Johanne Rodgers Ducibus, observavit et descripsit, Pars VII. Crustacea Anomoura. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Science of Philadelphia, 10 (4), 225 - 252. [pp. 63 - 90 on the reprint] https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 51447" type="journal article" year="1858">Stimpson, 1858</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(MNHN 
<accessionNumber id="AAE3AB77060A2E46FD50F9C7FCD32048" box="[735,825,1256,1282]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/B22041" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">B22041</accessionNumber>
) from Sydney Harbour and were therefore believed to be synonyms. 
<bibRefCitation id="D1214B65060A2E46FEB5F823FDBC206C" author="Guinot, D. &amp; Tavares, M." box="[314,598,1292,1319]" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" pagination="43 - 129" refId="ref26035" refString="Guinot, D. &amp; Tavares, M. (2003) A new subfamilial arrangement for the Dromiidae de Haan, 1833, with diagnoses and descriptions of new genera and species (Crustacea, Decapoda, Brachyura). Zoosystema, 25, 43 - 129." type="journal article" year="2003">Guinot &amp; Tavares (2003)</bibRefCitation>
argued that 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17060A2E46FD6BF822FC8A206C" authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1818" box="[740,864,1292,1318]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Dromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosa">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86060A2E46FD6BF822FC8A206C" box="[740,864,1292,1318]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">D. globosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
did not belong in 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17060A2E46FBBEF823FB22206C" authorityName="Borradaile" authorityYear="1900" box="[1073,1224,1292,1318]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Dromidiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86060A2E46FBBEF823FB22206C" box="[1073,1224,1292,1318]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Dromidiopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and erected a new genus, 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17060A2E46FF69F81FFE722000" authorityName="Guinot &amp; Tavares" authorityYear="2003" box="[230,408,1328,1354]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Lamarckdromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86060A2E46FF69F81FFE722000" box="[230,408,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Lamarckdromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, for this species. The key features of 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17060A2E46FCB4F81FFC072000" authorityName="Guinot &amp; Tavares" authorityYear="2003" box="[827,1005,1328,1354]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Lamarckdromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86060A2E46FCB4F81FFC072000" box="[827,1005,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Lamarckdromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are: all male abdominal segments free (last two fused in 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17060A2E46FED2F87BFE1E2024" authorityName="Borradaile" authorityYear="1900" box="[349,500,1364,1390]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Dromidiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86060A2E46FED2F87BFE1E2024" box="[349,500,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Dromidiopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), uropods concealed (versus uropods conspicuous), apertures of sternal grooves end between P2 (versus apertures end between P1) and uropods not used in the abdominal locking mechanism (versus uropods used to retain abdomen). The conclusion that 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17060A2E46FC89F8B3FBF020FC" baseAuthorityName="Lamarck" baseAuthorityYear="1818" box="[774,1050,1436,1462]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Lamarckdromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosa">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86060A2E46FC89F8B3FBF020FC" box="[774,1050,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Lamarckdromia globosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17060A2E46FABFF8B3FF112090" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Dromidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excavata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86060A2E46FABFF8B3FF112090" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Dromidia excavata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was reasonable at the time, given the fragmentary nature of the dried material, and because there was apparently only one Australian species. However, closer inspection of Australian material shows that there are two species, 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17060A2E46FF79FB27FD692369" authority="Stimpson, 1858" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[246,643,1544,1571]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Dromidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excavata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86060A2E46FF79FB27FE272368" box="[246,461,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Dromidia excavata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D1214B65060A2E46FE5CFB27FD692369" author="Stimpson, W." box="[467,643,1544,1571]" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" pagination="225 - 252" refId="ref30031" refString="Stimpson, W. (1858) Prodromus descriptionis animalium evertebratorum, quae in expeditione and Oceanum Pacificum Septentrionalem, a Republica Federata missa, Cadwaladaro Ringgold et Johanne Rodgers Ducibus, observavit et descripsit, Pars VII. Crustacea Anomoura. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Science of Philadelphia, 10 (4), 225 - 252. [pp. 63 - 90 on the reprint] https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 51447" type="journal article" year="1858">Stimpson, 1858</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and a new species described herein as 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17060A2E46FBB7FB27FAD62368" authority="Mclay &amp; Hosie, 2022" authorityName="Mclay &amp; Hosie" authorityYear="2022" box="[1080,1340,1544,1570]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Lamarckdromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beagle" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86060A2E46FBB7FB27FAD62368" box="[1080,1340,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Lamarckdromia beagle</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="87C4EA86060A2E46FACCFB27FA762368" bold="true" box="[1347,1436,1544,1570]" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9CF757FD060A2E46FACCFB27FA762368" box="[1347,1436,1544,1570]" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
It is not possible to say which, if any, of these two species might be synonymous with 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17060A2E46FBEAFB02FAF1230C" authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1818" box="[1125,1307,1580,1606]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Dromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosa">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86060A2E46FBEAFB02FAF1230C" box="[1125,1307,1580,1606]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Dromia globosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
so we conclude that in the absence of more intact specimens of this species it is best to resurrect the name 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17060A2E46FB49FB7FFA772320" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[1222,1437,1616,1642]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Dromidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excavata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86060A2E46FB49FB7FFA772320" box="[1222,1437,1616,1642]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Dromidia excavata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and conclude that there are three species in 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17060A2E46FD03FB5BFCD423C4" authorityName="Guinot &amp; Tavares" authorityYear="2003" box="[652,830,1652,1678]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Lamarckdromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="32" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86060A2E46FD03FB5BFCD423C4" box="[652,830,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="333">Lamarckdromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Morphological features of the species are compared in 2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
